experience.position: Research & Development Officer - IT Security & Compliance
experience.description:
As a pivotal member of the research division specializing in IT solutions for banks, financial institutions, and corporates, I played a crucial role in advancing business and technology development. This division spearheads the company's technological advancements and strategic partnerships, with a primary focus on expanding market shares, exploring new markets, and acquiring innovative solutions to enhance our portfolio and market coverage.

In my role as an R&D officer, I assumed the following responsibilities:

- Proactively initiating contact with potential partners to establish valuable collaborations and synergies.
- Conducting comprehensive evaluations of potential products and performing thorough competitor analyses within the industry.
- Requesting and coordinating product demonstrations to assess their suitability and effectiveness.
- Preparing detailed requirements for proof-of-concept (POC) projects, outlining specific objectives and success criteria.
- Leading the installation and conducting rigorous testing of intended solutions to ensure seamless integration and optimal performance.
- Leading the implementation of the sought solutions at the customer's site in various continents.

Through fulfilling these responsibilities, I actively contributed to driving technological innovation and strategic growth, positioning the company as a leader in the industry. Our ability to deliver cutting-edge solutions to clients in the banking, financial, and corporate sectors has been greatly enhanced by my efforts.

Networking:

I have supported over 500 clients, providing remote troubleshooting and technical issue resolution through email and phone. My expertise includes Cisco routers and switches configuration (VLANs, VPNs, ACLs, NAT). I have managed LAN, WAN, and VPN connections, organized racks, and implemented IPSec VPN tunnels.

Systems:

Specialized in implementing multi-factor authentication (MFA) solutions. Conducted environment assessments, ensured compatibility, and allocated bandwidth. Prepared project papers and documented processes. Installed, maintained, and provided support for MFA systems.

Network Monitoring Solutions:

Implemented WhatsUp Gold for network monitoring. Installed SNMP services, configured parameters, and integrated with routers/switches. Initiated notification services (email, SMS, push) for timely alerts. Conducted daily network health checks for uptime and stability.

VSAT Satellite Communications Technology:

Designed VSAT topologies for different environments. Conducted site surveys, prepared equipment, and developed scenarios. Installed, calibrated, and configured VSAT systems. Documented and provided training for first-level support.

My expertise in networking and systems has consistently delivered exceptional solutions, benefiting the organizations I have worked with.

Data scientist and ML engineer with over 8 years of experience. I have a passion for building ML-based solutions, from development to deployment. I love transforming an idea into a model, and a model into an API/product.

I have worked on different problems: financial derivative pricing, digital marketing analytics, deep learning for art generation, or demand prediction for on-line shopping. I have a background in pure mathematics and strong coding skills in Python.

experience.position: Machine Learning Engineer | Founding Talent Member

experience.description:
- Developed, deployed, and maintained a Machine Learning model to improve the efficiency of the shoppers' fleet.
- Bootstrapped the first data-warehouse and reporting layer in the company (Amazon Redshift + Amazon DMS + Tableau).

- Statistical analysis of financial markets using explainable Machine Learning techniques.
- Benchmarked a range of ML solutions to enhance model accuracy and explainability.
- Wrote a Python package to ensure the in-house reproducibility of each step of the analysis (data processing, data validation, data visualization, model construction, model validation, and model explanation).

- Developed and maintained the analytics dashboards for Cyngn's engineering team and Cyngn's clients.
- Developed components of the internal ETL tool in Python and SQL.
- Assisted the back-end engineer to integrate both frontend and backend of the analytics stack inside Amazon Redshift.

- Architected the first data-warehouse and reporting layer for our client.
- Developed several dashboards to help our client improve its fleet management efficiency.

- Optimization of performance marketing campaigns: reporting dashboards, ad-hoc data explorations/analysis, data engineering development, and machine learning model construction.

- Developed a neural network model to generate human realistic portraits of football players. The model was intended for use in the company's flagship game TopEleven, so robustness and QA constraints were added to the final pipeline. The model was finally used in the mobile game Golden Boot to generate a small number of samples.

- Designed game simulation systems in Python to ensure our games were both fun for our players and profitable for the company.

- Worked on the implementation of an internal tool to help our customer support team. The project was not finally completed and no impact on the company's result was achieved. The mistakes I made in this project helped me grow and become a better machine learning engineer.

Validation of mathematical models used in production by Erste Group Bank to estimate market risk and price financial contracts.

- Evaluation of the appropriateness of the mathematical framework used for the problem in hand, i.e. appropriateness of the stochastic process used to model the dynamics, suitability of the calibration strategy, benchmark with market best-practices.

- Own software implementation of the same mathematical model used in production and comparison of numerical results. Both real world and test cases are used to asses the accuracy of the production model.

- Proposal and implementation of a prototype model that improves the production model, if the last leaves substantial room for improvement.

- Writing of detailed documentation, from mathematical modelling to real-world impact of each model for the bank.

Mohand made a huge difference during his 3 months, bringing him into the team was a real game changer and he was quickly able to understand our deployment of Dynatrace and has started us on a journey of maturing and refining this to help us drive some real value. Mohand was also a huge help supporting the onboardong of a new perm monitoring specialist into the team. Without the knowledge that he had already picked up, this would have been a substantially greater challenge. 
The thanks and well wishes Mohand received from around our Digital team as well as from me are a great endorsement to both his approach and his expertise.

publications.title: Resolve Actions PRO - How to make REST API calls (and process the response)
publications.description:
Watch how quick and easy it is to make RESTful API calls in Resolve Actions PRO, and process the response to extract your required data - all without any code whatsoever.

For the more advanced, you can always get into the code to deal with more complex or unique edge use cases.  This is the power of Resolve Actions PRO.

publications.title: Resolve Actions PRO - Introduction to Runbooks
publications.description: Our definition of a 'runbook' may be slightly different to what you are used to, because a Resolve Actions PRO runbook can contain the automated workflow (that we call an "automation"), as well as an optional front-end web "page" that acts as the presentation layer to your automation.

publications.title: Resolve Actions - Introduction to Resolution Routing
publications.description:
Quickly learn how to use the Resolution Routing feature in Resolve Actions to automatically initiate a specific automation when triggered by a Resolve Gateway, email, URL, or custom URI (such as the HTTP Gateway Filter we created in a previous video).

This video refers to a previous video titled "Introduction to the HTTP Gateway" and can be found here:  https://youtu.be/0KfWx46WZp4

publications.title: Resolve Actions - Introduction to the HTTP Gateway
publications.description:
Quickly learn how the HTTP Gateway feature in Resolve Actions enables you to control how to ingest (or have 3rd-party tools push data) into Resolve.

The HTTP Gateway is similar to creating a webservice or URI endpoint that other tools can post data into Resolve (with the HTTP POST method).

Keep an eye out for Part 2 which introduces the Resolution Routing feature (https://youtu.be/ZqkByJMla6A).

publications.title: Resolve Actions - How to integrate with Microsoft Teams
publications.description:
Want to integrate ChatOps with your ITSM tool and already have Microsoft Teams? Use Resolve Actions to power ChatOps and modernize your service desk in minutes! Join Brent Hunter to see how you can quickly automate common tasks by combining these two tools.

In this demo, we show Resolve handling the incoming requests from the Teams chatbot:

- View my open tickets, update them, or close them.
- Reset my password
- Access Requests
- IT Health Dashboards
- Link to knowledge articles and guided assistance
- and pretty much anything you can think of!

publications.title: Resolve Actions - Compute - Expand Windows disk and VMWare VMDK file
publications.description: This video talks about the before & after changes, as well as a demonstration of how you can automate the expansion/extension of a Windows disk/volume and associated VMWare VMDK file.

publications.title: Resolve Actions - Service Desk - Create Meeting Room in Office 365 (Short Version)
publications.description: This is a demonstration video of a self-service input form for your end-users to create new Meeting Rooms in Office365 or Exchange Online.

publications.title: RESOLVE for Service Desk - Citrix Self-Service Troubleshooting
publications.description:
44% of Citrix Professionals and Businesses voted that frozen Citrix sessions were a consistent problem.

This video demonstrates how RESOLVE can provide an end-user with a self-service troubleshooting portal for common Citrix logon and connection issues.

Resolve issues faster by automating them with RESOLVE - the only automation platform you'll ever need.

publications.title: Demo Video: RESOLVE - How to create a new ServiceNow Catalog Item and configure the RESOLVE ServiceNow Gateway
publications.description:
This "how to" video describes the initial configuration of the RESOLVE ServiceNow Gateway to support Service Catalog Items and Requests coming into RESOLVE from ServiceNow.

We'll focus on the New Joiner Service Catalog item and how we get custom fields (or variables) from ServiceNow into RESOLVE - so we can use those values in our runbooks and automations.

publications.title: Demo Video: RESOLVE for Security - Email Phishing (and Security Case Management)
publications.description:
Learn how Security Analysts can solve email phishing security incidents faster, safer, and more reliably with RESOLVE Security Case Management, Orchestration & Automation, and the RESOLVE Security Module Automation Library.

RESOLVE includes Security Case Management to manage Security Investigations.  Automatically extract artefacts from an incoming email and orchestrate security tools to gain further threat intelligence.  Join all the dots to gather deep insight and initiate automation's and remediation immediately.

publications.description: See how we use our own RESOLVE automation platform internally to streamline the provisioning of new RESOLVE Evaluation instances on AWS.  RESOLVE creates the new instance, configures the networking and firewall rules, and informs the Sales Team and Customer of the connection details.

publications.description: Watch how RESOLVE integrates with many front-end tools to allow your end-users to reset their passwords - not just Windows and Active Directory - but also other independent and cloud-based services.

publications.title: 1E AppClarity ‚Äì Reclaiming Complex Applications
publications.description: 1E AppClarity has the advantage of being able to automatically uninstall applications that were originally installed using the Microsoft Windows Installer (MSI) technology. Using Microsoft ConfigMgr, an agentless AppClarity Reclaimer utility is advertised to the client computers. This utility queries the 1E AppClarity server for any unused applications for the local computer, and can then proceed to automatically uninstall these applications. Magic!

publications.title: Resolve Actions PRO - Introduction to Action Tasks
publications.description:
Learn more about what makes an Action Task in Resolve Actions PRO.
Action Tasks are the fundamental building blocks of an automation or runbook.  An action task performs a specific function, and usually returns some sort of output (so you use that data later on in your automation, or to change the flow of your automation).

publications.title: Disentangling Linguistic Features with Dimension-Wise Analysis of Vector Embeddings
publications.publishedAt: Proceedings of the 5th Workshop on Trustworthy NLP (TrustNLP 2025) ¬∑ May 1, 2025
publications.description: Understanding the inner workings of neural embeddings, particularly in models such as BERT, remains a challenge because of their high-dimensional and opaque nature. This paper proposes a framework for uncovering the specific dimensions of vector embeddings that encode distinct linguistic properties (LPs). We introduce the Linguistically Distinct Sentence Pairs (LDSP-10) dataset, which isolates ten key linguistic features such as synonymy, negation, tense, and quantity. Using this dataset, we analyze BERT embeddings with various methods, including the Wilcoxon signed-rank test, mutual information, and recursive feature elimination, to identify the most influential dimensions for each LP. We introduce a new metric, the Embedding Dimension Impact (EDI) score, which quantifies the relevance of each embedding dimension to a LP. Our findings show that certain properties, such as negation and polarity, are robustly encoded in specific dimensions, while others, like synonymy, exhibit more complex patterns. This study provides insights into the interpretability of embeddings, which can guide the development of more transparent and optimized language models, with implications for model bias mitigation and the responsible deployment of AI systems.

headline: Technologist | Collaborator | Ultrarunner | Father | Problem Solver | Vim
about:
Technologist.  Collaborator.  Problem solver.  I seek hard challenges both at work and in the mountains.

Come join me on the trails!  http://goo.gl/P9TAEq

For Work :: I am happily creating my own reality at Okteto (Startup & YC'19 graduate).  On any given day, I have a chance to satisfy our Customers, support our worldwide Sales Teams, and write code to extend our application.  I love waking up each day having the opportunity to collaborate with Engineering, Operations, Marketing, and Initiative Owners on immediate business needs.

For Fun :: Like @ work, I seek out some of the toughest challenges and thrive on completion.  Most recently, I finished Javelina Jundred, a 100M race in the Arizona Desert (@29hr), the epic Ultra Race of Champions 100K in Auburn CA (@19hrs), Bandera 100K, Sean O'Brien 50M, Canyons 100K, Rio Del Lago 100M and others.  I am also an entrant to the oldest and most legendary ultramarathon Western States 100M in Auburn CA.

Me :: I am a passionate and pragmatic hands-on technologist with a diverse background in both developing and selling enterprise software. Over 10 years of experience designing, developing, and maintaining high transaction, server-side Internet applications.  Most recently, I've enjoyed the last 15 years collaborating with sales teams to enable Customers with best-in-class software development tools and experiences.

In a nutshell :: vim over emacs. ruby over java.  95+ wpm. inspect and adapt. failure over indecisiveness. wisdom of crowds. evolutionary design over up front planning. maintainable software survives. dynamically typed languages rock. wake up excited. learn something new every day.

Specialties: agile . people . vim . snowboarding . ruby . linux . javascript . tmux . juggling . ultramarathons

experience.description:

AI assistance in PR/MRs to analyze content for code improvements, code reviews, and correctness to accelerate acceptance.

GitLab.  Y-combinator graduate.

Capture Ideas.  Prioritize.  Build.  Deploy. Monitor.   All from a *single* application.

Stoked (!!!) to help our Customers evolve, amp up on modern tech, stay relevant, and survive.

green screen. vim. tmux. ruby. linux. javascript.... all day long.

publications.title: Solving ImageNet: a Unified Scheme for Training any Backbone to Top Results
publications.description: ImageNet serves as the primary dataset for evaluating the quality of computer-vision models. The common practice today is training each architecture with a tailor-made scheme, designed and tuned by an expert. In this paper, we present a unified scheme for training any backbone on ImageNet. The scheme, named USI (Unified Scheme for ImageNet), is based on knowledge distillation and modern tricks. It requires no adjustments or hyper-parameters tuning between different models, and is efficient in terms of training times. We test USI on a wide variety of architectures, including CNNs, Transformers, Mobile-oriented and MLP-only. On all models tested, USI outperforms previous state-of-the-art results. Hence, we are able to transform training on ImageNet from an expert-oriented task to an automatic seamless routine. Since USI accepts any backbone and trains it to top results, it also enables to perform methodical comparisons, and identify the most efficient backbones along the speed-accuracy Pareto curve. Implementation is available at:https://github.com/Alibaba-MIIL/Solving_ImageNet

publications.title: TResNet: High Performance GPU-Dedicated Architecture
publications.description: Many deep learning models, developed in recent years, reach higher ImageNet accuracy than ResNet50, with fewer or comparable FLOPS count. While FLOPs are often seen as a proxy for network efficiency, when measuring actual GPU training and inference throughput, vanilla ResNet50 is usually significantly faster than its recent competitors, offering better throughput-accuracy trade-off. In this work, we introduce a series of architecture modifications that aim to boost neural networks' accuracy, while retaining their GPU training and inference efficiency. We first demonstrate and discuss the bottlenecks induced by FLOPs-optimizations. We then suggest alternative designs that better utilize GPU structure and assets. Finally, we introduce a new family of GPU-dedicated models, called TResNet, which achieve better accuracy and efficiency than previous ConvNets. Using a TResNet model, with similar GPU throughput to ResNet50, we reach 80.7% top-1 accuracy on ImageNet. Our TResNet models also transfer well and achieve state-of-the-art accuracy on competitive datasets such as Stanford cars (96.0%), CIFAR-10 (99.0%), CIFAR-100 (91.5%) and Oxford-Flowers (99.1%). Implementation is available at: this https URL

publications.title: Compact Network Training for Person ReID
publications.publishedAt: International Conference on Multimedia Retrieval (ICMR) 2020 (Oral) ¬∑ Oct 15, 2019
publications.description:
The task of person re-identification (ReID) has attracted growing attention in recent years with improving performance but lack of focus on real-world applications. 
Most state of the art methods use large pre-trained models, e.g., ResNet50 (~25M parameters), as their backbone, which makes it tedious to explore different architecture modifications. 
In this study, we focus on small-sized randomly initialized models which enable us to easily introduce network and training modifications suitable for person ReID public datasets and real-world setups. 
We show the robustness of our network and training improvements by outperforming state of the art results in terms of rank-1 accuracy and mAP on Market1501 (96.2, 89.7) and DukeMTMC (89.8, 80.3) with only 6.4M parameters and without using re-ranking.
Finally, we show the applicability of the proposed ReID network for multi-object tracking.

Olric provides a simple way to create a fast, scalable, and shared pool of RAM across a cluster of machines. It's a distributed, in-memory key/value store and cache, written entirely in Go and designed specifically for distributed environments.

https://github.com/olric-data/olric

Flexible Deployment:

* Embedded Go Library: Integrate Olric directly into your Go applications.
* Standalone Service: Run Olric as a language-independent service.

Key Features:

* Effortless Scalability: Designed to handle hundreds of members and thousands of clients. New nodes auto-discover the cluster and linearly increase capacity.

* Automatic Distribution: Provides partitioning (sharding) and data re-balancing out-of-the-box, requiring no external coordination services. Data and backups are automatically balanced when capacity is added.

* Wide Client Support: Uses the standard Redis Serialization Protocol (RESP), ensuring client libraries are available in nearly all major programming languages.

* Common Use Cases: Ideal for distributed caching, managing application cluster state, and implementing publish-subscribe messaging.

headline: Senior Software Engineer
about:
I‚Äôm a Senior Software Engineer at Ambassador Labs, contributing across the full stack with a focus on building robust developer tooling and experiences. I work primarily with Go, Next.js, and Postgres, driving development across both the backend and frontend.

My recent work includes extending our CLI and API with new features in Go, as well as enhancing our UI using Next.js to deliver seamless user experiences. I‚Äôve also been involved in integrating AI capabilities into developer environments by working with MCP clients and servers to power intelligent features in editors like VS Code and Cursor.

I highly value building tools that make developers more productive and efficient, with a focus on clean architecture, usability, and performance.

experience.description:
As a Senior Software Engineer at Ambassador Labs, I‚Äôve been leading and contributing to full-stack development initiatives focused on enhancing developer productivity through powerful tooling. My core tech stack includes Go, Next.js, and Postgres, and I work across the CLI, API, and UI layers of our platform.

One of my primary responsibilities has been developing new capabilities in the CLI and backend systems using Go. This includes robust integration with OpenAPI specs and managing API lifecycles using the blackbird CLI, where I automated the processing of complex, nested specifications. On the frontend, I‚Äôve delivered new user-facing features and improvements in Next.js to support a seamless experience.

I've also spent some time developing a VS Code extension for expanding the developer footprint of the Blackbird system to allow developers to access Blackbird where they work, without having to run standalone CLI applications.

A area of recent focus has been the research/integration of AI-powered development tools. I‚Äôve worked with MCP clients and servers to enable advanced features in editors like VS Code and Cursor, bridging our platform‚Äôs capabilities with intelligent in-editor assistance.

I‚Äôve also been actively involved in building and supporting internal developer tools, including exploring IDE extensions, CLI workflows, and systematized logging/reporting mechanisms.

Promoted to lead architecture and technical direction for a suite of .NET microservices on AWS.

Drove the framework upgrade from .NET Core 3 to .NET 6, improving performance, maintainability, and developer velocity.

Integrated Dynatrace for real-time monitoring and diagnostics, enabling faster issue resolution.

Used dotTrace and dotMemory to identify and fix performance bottlenecks in production systems.

Integrated Recurly to support seamless billing and subscription workflows.

Contributed to architectural decisions and collaborated closely with product and operations teams to deliver business-critical features.

Effectively leading a team in an agile environment in the design and development of platform enhancements across .NET desktop and web technologies. Act as Scrum Master by leading the end-to-end agile process to deliver features to the customer to the criteria specified by product.

Hold yearly performance reviews for the team as well as regular 1:1 meetings to provide advice, guidance and support to achieve effective resolution of concerns or challenges. This is also where we take time to ensure the needs of the individuals are being met and that they are making progress towards their and the companies aligned goals.

Involvement in the recruitment process hiring new developers as well as reviewing applications for positions.

Coordinate strategic planning, design and development across Product/UX/Architecture/Content teams to ensure all parties are aware of ongoing developments and that any issues are addressed as early in the development cycle as possible.

Part of the Process Improvement Group which was a cross-functional team formed to identify and implement process improvements from the ground up, across all areas of Cherwell.

Design and development of features and bugfixes for the Cherwell Service Management platform. Participant in code-reviews and provide feedback to other developers about design choices.

I had the privilege of working closely with Jyoti Mittal at Wipro, and I can say without hesitation that she is one of the most reliable, skilled, and dedicated performance testing professionals I‚Äôve come across.

What always stood out to me about Jyoti was not just her deep technical knowledge, but the calm, methodical way she approached even the most complex challenges. Whether it was designing a performance strategy from scratch or diagnosing critical system bottlenecks under pressure, she handled everything with precision and confidence. Her expertise spans a wide range of tools‚ÄîLoadRunner, JMeter, Neoload, Dynatrace, AppDynamics, Splunk‚Äîand she uses them with real insight, not just surface-level know-how.

Jyoti‚Äôs contributions were instrumental in delivering several high-stakes projects for large banking and insurance clients across the UK, Australia, and South Africa. She doesn‚Äôt just execute tasks‚Äîshe takes full ownership, always looking at the bigger picture and aligning her work with business goals. I‚Äôve seen her proactively raise risks, mentor junior engineers, and collaborate seamlessly across teams, especially in agile environments.

What makes her stand out even more is her humility and team spirit. Despite her vast experience, Jyoti is always approachable, always willing to help, and genuinely invested in the success of the team. Working with her was not just professionally rewarding‚Äîit was personally enjoyable as well.

Any team would be lucky to have someone with her combination of technical depth, leadership, and integrity. I wholeheartedly recommend Jyoti for any performance engineering or leadership role.

I worked on a team that handles regression prevention between product releases. In between releases, all of our customer tests are run on each version of the product, to ensure that no major changes occur between the results that may indicate a bug in our development. 

My project dealt with solving the problem of the amount of data they had to process. The team performed vast amounts of manual analysis on the data, all in the span of a few weeks. This was manageable some time ago, but the number of customer tests we are running has expanded rapidly, and they needed to scale the process. 

To do this, we worked on utilizing a no-SQL database, HBase, to find a new way to store our data, and to use Machine Learning to cut down on the amount of manual analysis necessary. My project focused on creating the bridge between HBase and the Machine Learning algorithm. I facilitated the creation of the HBase table via a tool called Phoenix, a relational database layer over HBase. I populated that table with our test result data, filtered and deduped the data, and turned that data into a SequenceFile as input to the Machine Learning algorithm they had developed.

publications.title: Ratcheted Encryption and Key Exchange: The Security of Messaging
publications.description: We give a theoretical treatment of ratcheting, lifting it from a technique used in secure messaging protocols to a cryptographic primitive. To allow a modular treatment, we decouple the creation of keys from their use. We define ratcheted key exchange and give a protocol proven to achieve it. We then define ratcheted encryption and show how to achieve it generically from ratcheted key exchange and standard encryption.
